Class PassThruIfNullOrElse<I,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • no.motif.f.base.PassThruIfNullOrElse<I,O>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Fn<I,O>, PartialApplicableTo<Fn0<O>>

    public abstract class PassThruIfNullOrElse<I,O>
extends Object
implements Fn<I,O>
    A convenient base implementation of Fn which implements no operation (NOP) for null values. For any non-null, the function value is passed to $nullsafe(Object), which can be implemented without any regard to possible null-pointers. When the function is passed a null value, it returns null, thus adhering to a simple "garbage in ‐> garbage out" policy.

    Fn, Serialized Form
